    {
      "id": 70845,
      "name": "Claude De Vetter",
      "username": "MedTechCD",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/57b2e6/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-02-11T15:06:20.007Z",
      "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"dermate\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"55093\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ea666f/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> dermate:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Trainer is connected with a Garmin Edge 830 unit via ANT+ during training</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Make absolutely sure that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The Edge 830 is connected in ANT+ and not in BLE</li>\n<li>The Edge 830 does not connect the trainer as \u2018trainer\u2019 but as \u2018sensor\u2019</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You should <strong>not</strong> have a trainer connected to your Edge 830 because it could be taking control. You should only see the trainer\u2019s power/speed/cadence in the sensor menu of the Edge.</p>\n<p>If in doubt, turn your Edge off and check if TD can connect.</p>",
