    {
      "id": 71354,
      "name": "Claude De Vetter",
      "username": "MedTechCD",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/57b2e6/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2025-02-16T13:06:52.395Z",
      "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"dermate\" data-post=\"14\" data-topic=\"55093\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ea666f/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> dermate:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Garmin Edge connection is mandatory</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Don\u00b4t pair your trainer as \u00b4trainer\u00b4 on your Garmin! Go to the sensor menu and look for \u00b4sensors\u00b4.<br>\nThen Garmin will only read from your trainer sensor broadcast.<br>\nElse you risk that Garmin will try to control your trainer and you get a conflict with TD who wants to control the trainer.</p>",
